### Health: process is alive even before a model artifact exists.
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/health

### Readiness: confirms whether a valid artifact is loaded.
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/ready

### Metadata: available after `make train` and API startup.
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/metadata

### Predict: binary predictions and positive-class probabilities.
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/predict
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "features": [
    [0.0, 0.0],
    [1.0, 1.0]
  ]
}

### Validation example: wrong feature count should return an error.
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/predict
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "features": [
    [0.0, 0.0, 0.0]
  ]
}
